  "myria": {
    metadata: { title: "What Is Myria (MYRIA)? Price, Guide & How to Buy (2026) | degen0x", description: "Learn about Myria (MYRIA), the Ethereum Layer 2 scaling solution for blockchain gaming. Discover MYRIA tokenomics and how to buy." },
    props: {
      title: "What Is Myria (MYRIA)? Price, Guide & How to Buy",
      categoryName: "Investing",
      categorySlug: "investing",
      readTime: "8 min read",
      intro: "Myria (MYRIA) is an Ethereum Layer 2 scaling solution purpose-built for blockchain gaming. Using zk-rollup technology powered by StarkWare, Myria offers gasless transactions and instant trade confirmations optimized for gaming workloads. The platform includes a game development SDK, NFT marketplace, and a growing library of games built on its infrastructure.",
    },
    toc: [ { id: "what-is", title: "what-is", level: 2 }, { id: "what-is-myria", title: "What Is Myria?", level: 2 }, { id: "how-it-works", title: "how-it-works", level: 2 }, { id: "how-does-myria-work", title: "How Does Myria Work?", level: 2 }, { id: "tokenomics", title: "tokenomics", level: 2 }, { id: "myria-tokenomics", title: "MYRIA Tokenomics", level: 2 }, { id: "use-cases", title: "use-cases", level: 2 }, { id: "key-use-cases", title: "Key Use Cases", level: 2 }, { id: "how-to-buy", title: "how-to-buy", level: 2 }, { id: "how-to-buy-myria", title: "How to Buy MYRIA", level: 2 }, { id: "risks", title: "risks", level: 2 }, { id: "risks-and-considerations", title: "Risks and Considerations", level: 2 } ],
    faqs: [{question:"What is Myria?",answer:"Myria is an Ethereum L2 scaling solution for blockchain gaming using zk-rollup technology. MYRIA is the utility token for the platform used in governance, staking, and gaming transactions."},{question:"Where can I buy MYRIA?",answer:"MYRIA is available on KuCoin, Gate.io, and other exchanges. It can also be acquired through Myria ecosystem activities."},{question:"Is Myria a good investment?",answer:"Myria offers gaming-specific L2 infrastructure on Ethereum. Its value depends on attracting quality games and players to the platform in a competitive blockchain gaming landscape."}],
    relatedArticles: [{title:"Best Cryptos to Buy",href:"/investing/best/cryptos-to-buy",category:"Investing"},{title:"How to Invest in Crypto",href:"/investing/learn/how-to-invest-in-crypto",category:"Investing"}],
    childrenHtml: `<section id="what-is"><h2>What Is Myria?</h2><p>Myria is a blockchain gaming platform that combines Layer 2 scaling technology with game development tools and a marketplace. The L2 solution uses StarkWare's STARK proof technology to batch thousands of transactions into a single Ethereum proof, enabling the high throughput and zero gas fees necessary for gaming. Myria Studios develops first-party games while third-party developers can build on the platform using the Myria SDK.</p><p>The platform focuses on making blockchain gaming accessible by abstracting away the complexity of wallets, gas fees, and token management. Games built on Myria aim to provide Web2-quality experiences with Web3 ownership benefits, targeting both crypto-native gamers and mainstream audiences new to blockchain gaming.</p></section>
      <section id="how-it-works"><h2>How Does Myria Work?</h2><p>Myria's L2 processes up to 9,000 transactions per second with zero gas fees for users. The platform provides developers with APIs and SDKs to integrate NFT minting, trading, and wallet management into their games. The Myria marketplace enables cross-game NFT trading. Players create a Myria wallet that works across all games on the platform. The infrastructure handles the blockchain complexity so players can focus on gameplay while still benefiting from true digital ownership of their in-game assets.</p></section>
      <section id="tokenomics"><h2>MYRIA Tokenomics</h2><p>MYRIA has a total supply of 50 billion tokens distributed across ecosystem rewards, node operators, team, and investors. The token features staking for node operators who help validate transactions on the L2 network. Token utility includes governance votes, staking rewards, marketplace transactions, and in-game purchases. The large total supply reflects the need for a high-volume gaming currency that supports micro-transactions across many games.</p></section>
      <section id="use-cases"><h2>Key Use Cases</h2><p>MYRIA is used for platform governance, node operator staking, marketplace transaction fees, in-game purchases across Myria games, and developer incentives. The token connects the L2 infrastructure with the gaming and marketplace layers of the ecosystem.</p></section>
      <section id="how-to-buy"><h2>How to Buy MYRIA</h2><p>MYRIA is available on KuCoin, Gate.io, and other exchanges. After purchasing, MYRIA can be used within the Myria ecosystem or staked for rewards. Store in the Myria Wallet or MetaMask connected to the Myria L2.</p></section>
      <section id="risks"><h2>Risks and Considerations</h2><p>Myria competes with established gaming L2s like Immutable X (also built on StarkWare), Ronin, and general-purpose L2s expanding into gaming. The large token supply means price appreciation requires substantial demand growth. First-party games are still in development with uncertain market reception. The gaming L2 space is crowded and consolidation is likely, with no guarantee Myria will emerge as a winner. Developer adoption is critical but challenging when competing platforms offer similar tools. The project needs to demonstrate clear advantages over competitors to attract both developers and players.</p></section>`,
  },
